  19 /* The GB18030 standard was re-released on Nov. 2000 and many code values
  20  * were changed. The reimplementation of this module is based on the info
  21  * from Markus Scherer's site:
  22  * http://oss.software.ibm.com/cvs/icu/~checkout~/icu/source/tools/makeconv/gb18030/gb18030.html
  23  *
  24  *   Original - Yong Li <rigel863@yahoo.com>  Jan. 28, 2001

  32 /* The tables in this file are generated from the charmap.
  33    In a first step, the charmap is converted to a simple table format:
  34 
  35       ./tst-table-charmap.sh GB18030 < ../localedata/charmaps/GB18030 \
  36       > GB18030.table
  37 */
  38 
  39 /* Table for GB18030 -> UCS-4, containing the two-byte characters only.
  40    Generated through
  41 
  42    clisp tab.lisp < GB18030.table
  43 
  44    where tab.lisp is:
  45    ;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
  46    (locally (declare (compile))
  47      (let ((count 0))
  48        (loop
  49      (let ((line (read-line nil nil nil)))
  50        (unless line (return))
  51        (when (eql (position #\Tab line) 6)
  52          (let ((gbk (parse-integer line :start 2 :end 6 :radix 16))
  53            (ucs (parse-integer line :start 9 :radix 16)))
  54            (when (<= ucs #xffff)
  55          (when (= (mod count 4) 0)
  56            (format t " "))
  57          (format t " ~([0x~4,'0X] = 0x~4,'0X~),"
  58                (let ((ch1 (ldb (byte 8 8) gbk))
  59                  (ch2 (ldb (byte 8 0) gbk)))
  60                  (+ (* (- ch1 #x81) 192) (- ch2 #x40)))
  61                ucs)
  62          (incf count)
  63          (when (= (mod count 4) 0)
  64            (format t "~%")))))))
  65        (format t "~%")))
  66    ;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
  67 */
  68

9091 /* Table for UCS-4 -> GB18030, for the range U+0080..U+9FBB.
9092    There are three kinds of two-byte entries (ch1, ch2):
9093      (ch1, ch2) = (0, 0) means an unmapped character,
9094      0x20 <= ch1 <= 0x80 means a four-byte character,
9095      ch1 >= 0x81 means a two-byte character.
9096    Generated through
9097 
9098    sort -k 2 < GB18030.table | clisp tab.lisp
9099 
9100    where tab.lisp is:
9101    ;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
9102    (locally (declare (compile))
9103      (let ((count 0)
9104        (range-start #x0080) (range-end #x9FBB))
9105        (flet ((output-pair (ucs entry)
9106         (when (= (mod count 3) 0)
9107           (format t " "))
9108         (format t " ~([0x~4,'0X] = \"\\x~2,'0X\\x~2,'0X\"~),"
9109             ; There are two ranges. The gap length is:
9110             ;   (- #xd7a4 #xac00) = 11172.
9111             (cond ((<= range-start ucs range-end)
9112                    (- ucs range-start)))
9113             (ash entry -8) (ldb (byte 8 0) entry))
9114         (incf count)
9115         (when (= (mod count 3) 0)
9116           (format t "~%"))))
9117      (loop
9118        (let ((line (read-line nil nil nil)))
9119          (unless line (return))
9120          (when (eql (position #\Tab line) 6)
9121            (let* ((gbk (parse-integer line :start 2 :end 6 :radix 16))
9122               (ucs (parse-integer line :start 9 :radix 16)))
9123          (when (<= range-start ucs range-end)
9124            (assert (>= gbk #x8100))
9125            (output-pair ucs gbk))))
9126          (when (eql (position #\Tab line) 10)
9127            (let* ((gbk (parse-integer line :start 2 :end 10 :radix 16))
9128               (ucs (parse-integer line :start 13 :radix 16))
9129               (ch1 (ldb (byte 8 24) gbk))
9130               (ch2 (ldb (byte 8 16) gbk))
9131               (ch3 (ldb (byte 8 8) gbk))
9132               (ch4 (ldb (byte 8 0) gbk))
9133               (linear (+ (* (+ (* (+ (* (- ch1 #x81) 10)
9134                          (- ch2 #x30))
9135                       126)
9136                        (- ch3 #x81))
9137                     10)
9138                  (- ch4 #x30))))
9139          (when (<= range-start ucs range-end)
9140            (output-pair ucs (+ #x2000 linear))))))))
9141        (format t "~%")))
9142    ;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
9143 */

22738 /* Table for UCS-4 -> GB18030, for the range U+E000..U+FFFF.
22739    There are three kinds of two-byte entries (ch1, ch2):
22740      (ch1, ch2) = (0, 0) means an unmapped character,
22741      0x20 <= ch1 <= 0x80 means a four-byte character,
22742      ch1 >= 0x81 means a two-byte character.
22743    Generated through
22744 
22745    sort -k 2 < GB18030.table | clisp tab.lisp
22746 
22747    where tab.lisp is:
22748    ;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
22749    (locally (declare (compile))
22750      (let ((count 0)
22751        (range-start #xE000) (range-end #xFFFF)
22752        (gap-start #xE865) (gap-end #xF92C))
22753        (flet ((output-pair (ucs entry)
22754         (when (= (mod count 3) 0)
22755           (format t " "))
22756         (format t " ~([0x~4,'0X] = \"\\x~2,'0X\\x~2,'0X\"~),"
22757             (cond ((<= ucs #xe864) (- ucs range-start))
22758                   (t (- ucs range-start 4295)))
22759             (ash entry -8) (ldb (byte 8 0) entry))
22760         (incf count)
22761         (when (= (mod count 3) 0)
22762           (format t "~%"))))
22763      (loop
22764        (let ((line (read-line nil nil nil)))
22765          (unless line (return))
22766          (when (eql (position #\Tab line) 6)
22767            (let* ((gbk (parse-integer line :start 2 :end 6 :radix 16))
22768               (ucs (parse-integer line :start 9 :radix 16)))
22769          (when (<= range-start ucs range-end)
22770            (assert (>= gbk #x8100))
22771            (output-pair ucs gbk))))
22772          (when (eql (position #\Tab line) 10)
22773            (let* ((gbk (parse-integer line :start 2 :end 10 :radix 16))
22774               (ucs (parse-integer line :start 13 :radix 16))
22775               (ch1 (ldb (byte 8 24) gbk))
22776               (ch2 (ldb (byte 8 16) gbk))
22777               (ch3 (ldb (byte 8 8) gbk))
22778               (ch4 (ldb (byte 8 0) gbk))
22779               (linear (+ (* (+ (* (+ (* (- ch1 #x81) 10)
22780                          (- ch2 #x30))
22781                       126)
22782                        (- ch3 #x81))
22783                     10)
22784                  (- ch4 #x30))))
22785          (when (and (<= range-start ucs range-end)
22786                 (not (<= gap-start ucs gap-end)))
22787            (assert (>= linear 7457))
22788            (assert (< (- linear 7456) #x8100))
22789            (output-pair ucs (- linear 7456))))))))
22790        (format t "~%")))
22791    ;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
22792 */

24090 /* Definitions used in the body of the `gconv' function.  */
24091 #define CHARSET_NAME        "GB18030//"
24092 #define FROM_LOOP       from_gb18030
24093 #define TO_LOOP         to_gb18030
24094 #define DEFINE_INIT     1
24095 #define DEFINE_FINI     1
24096 #define MIN_NEEDED_FROM     1
24097 #define MAX_NEEDED_FROM     4
24098 #define MIN_NEEDED_TO       4
24099 #define ONE_DIRECTION       0
24100 
24101 
24102 /* First define the conversion function from GB18030 to UCS4.  */
24103 #define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT    MIN_NEEDED_FROM
24104 #define MAX_NEEDED_INPUT    MAX_NEEDED_FROM
24105 #define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT   MIN_NEEDED_TO
24106 #define LOOPFCT         FROM_LOOP
24107 #define BODY \
24108   {                                       \
24109     uint32_t ch = *inptr;                             \
24110                                           \
24111     if (ch <= 0x7f)                               \
24112       ++inptr;                                    \
24113     else                                      \
24114       if (ch < 0x81 || ch > 0xfe)                         \
24115     {                                     \
24116       /* This is illegal.  */                         \
24117       STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1);                     \
24118     }                                     \
24119       else                                    \
24120     {                                     \
24121       /* Two or four byte character.  First test whether the next         \
24122          byte is also available.  */                      \
24123       uint32_t ch2;                               \
24124       unsigned long int idx;                          \
24125                                           \
24126       if (inptr + 1 >= inend)                         \
24127         {                                     \
24128           /* The second byte is not available.  Store the             \
24129          intermediate result.  */                     \
24130           result = __GCONV_INCOMPLETE_INPUT;                  \
24131           break;                                  \
24132         }                                     \
24133                                           \
24134       ch2 = inptr[1];                             \
24135                                           \
24136       /* All second bytes of a multibyte character must be >= 0x30. */    \
24137       if (ch2 < 0x30)                             \
24138         STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (2);                   \
24139                                           \
24140       if (ch2 >= 0x30 && ch2 <= 0x39)                     \
24141         {                                     \
24142           /* A four-byte character */                     \
24143           uint32_t ch3;                           \
24144           uint32_t ch4;                           \
24145                                           \
24146           if (inptr + 3 >= inend)                         \
24147         {                                 \
24148           /* Not all bytes are available.  Store              \
24149              the intermediate result.  */                 \
24150           result = __GCONV_INCOMPLETE_INPUT;                  \
24151           break;                              \
24152         }                                 \
24153                                           \
24154           ch3 = inptr[2];                             \
24155                                           \
24156           if (ch3 < 0x81 || ch3 > 0xfe)                   \
24157         {                                 \
24158           /* This is an illegal character.  */                \
24159           STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (3);                 \
24160         }                                 \
24161                                           \
24162           ch4 = inptr[3];                             \
24163                                           \
24164           if (ch4 < 0x30 || ch4 > 0x39)                   \
24165         {                                 \
24166           /* This is an illegal character.  */                \
24167           STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (4);                 \
24168         }                                 \
24169           idx = (((ch - 0x81) * 10 + (ch2 - 0x30)) * 126              \
24170               + ch3 - 0x81) * 10 + ch4 - 0x30;                \
24171                                           \
24172           if (idx <= 0x333)                           \
24173         ch = __fourbyte_to_ucs[idx];                      \
24174           else if (idx >= 0x334 && idx <= 0x1d20)                 \
24175         ch = idx + 0x11e;                         \
24176           else if (idx >= 0x1d21 && idx <= 0x2402)                \
24177         ch = __fourbyte_to_ucs[idx - 6637];               \
24178           else if (idx >= 0x2403 && idx <= 0x2c40)                \
24179         ch = idx + 0x240;                         \
24180           else if (idx >= 0x2c41 && idx <= 0x4a78)                \
24181         ch = __fourbyte_to_ucs[idx - 6637 - 2110];            \
24182           else if (idx >= 0x4a79 && idx <= 0x82bc)                \
24183         ch = idx + 0x5543;                        \
24184           else if (idx >= 0x82bd && idx <= 0x830d)                \
24185         ch = __fourbyte_to_ucs[idx - 6637 - 2110 - 14404];        \
24186           else if (idx >= 0x830e && idx <= 0x93d4)                \
24187         ch = idx + 0x6557;                        \
24188           else if (idx >= 0x93d5 && idx <= 0x99e1)                \
24189         ch = __fourbyte_to_ucs[idx - 6637 - 2110 - 14404 - 4295];     \
24190           else if (idx >= 0x99e2 && idx <= 0x99fb)                \
24191         ch = idx + 0x6604;                        \
24192           else if (idx >= 0x2e248 && idx <= 0x12e247)             \
24193         ch = idx - 0x1e248;                       \
24194           else                                \
24195         ch = 0;                               \
24196                                           \
24197           if (ch == 0 && *inptr != '\0')                      \
24198         {                                 \
24199           /* This is an illegal character.  */                \
24200           STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (4);                 \
24201         }                                 \
24202                                           \
24203           inptr += 4;                             \
24204         }                                     \
24205       else if (__glibc_likely (ch2 >= 0x40))                  \
24206         {                                     \
24207           /* A two-byte character */                      \
24208           idx = (ch - 0x81) * 192 + (ch2 - 0x40);                 \
24209                                           \
24210           if (idx > 0x5E7E                            \
24211           || (ch = __twobyte_to_ucs[idx],                 \
24212               ch == 0 && *inptr != '\0'))                 \
24213         {                                 \
24214           /* Handle a few special cases.  */                  \
24215           if (idx == 0x5dd1)                          \
24216             ch = 0x20087;                         \
24217           else if (idx == 0x5dd2)                     \
24218             ch = 0x20089;                         \
24219           else if (idx == 0x5dd3)                     \
24220             ch = 0x200cc;                         \
24221           else if (idx == 0x5dec)                     \
24222             ch = 0x215D7;                         \
24223           else if (idx == 0x5df6)                     \
24224             ch = 0x2298F;                         \
24225           else if (idx == 0x5e11)                     \
24226             ch = 0x241FE;                         \
24227           else                                \
24228             {                                 \
24229               /* This is an illegal character.  */            \
24230               STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (2);             \
24231             }                                 \
24232         }                                 \
24233                                           \
24234           inptr += 2;                             \
24235         }                                     \
24236       else                                    \
24237         {                                     \
24238           /* This is an illegal character.  */                \
24239           STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (2);                 \
24240         }                                     \
24241     }                                     \
24242                                           \
24243     *((uint32_t *) outptr) = ch;                          \
24244     outptr += sizeof (uint32_t);                          \
24245   }
24246 #define LOOP_NEED_FLAGS
24247 #define ONEBYTE_BODY \
24248   {                                       \
24249     if (c < 0x80)                                 \
24250       return c;                                   \
24251     else                                      \
24252       return WEOF;                                \
24253   }
24254 #include <iconv/loop.c>

24257 /* Next, define the other direction.  */
24258 #define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT    MIN_NEEDED_TO
24259 #define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT   MIN_NEEDED_FROM
24260 #define MAX_NEEDED_OUTPUT   MAX_NEEDED_FROM
24261 #define LOOPFCT         TO_LOOP
24262 #define BODY \
24263   {                                       \
24264     uint32_t ch = *((const uint32_t *) inptr);                    \
24265                                           \
24266     if (ch <= 0x7f)                               \
24267       /* It's plain ASCII.  */                            \
24268       *outptr++ = (unsigned char) ch;                         \
24269     else                                      \
24270       {                                       \
24271     unsigned long int idx = 0;                        \
24272     const unsigned char *cp = NULL;                       \
24273     int len = 2;    /* This is the most common case.  */              \
24274     if (ch <= 0x9FBB)                             \
24275       {                                   \
24276         cp = __ucs_to_gb18030_tab1[ch - 0x80];                \
24277         if (*cp && *cp < 0x81)                        \
24278           {                                   \
24279         idx = (cp[0] - 0x20) * 256 + cp[1];               \
24280         len = 4;                              \
24281           }                                   \
24282         if (cp[0] == 0 && cp[1] == 0)                     \
24283           len = 0;                                \
24284       }                                   \
24285     else if (ch >= 0x9fbc && ch <= 0xD7ff)                    \
24286       {                                   \
24287         idx = ch - 0x5543;                            \
24288         len = 4;                                  \
24289       }                                   \
24290     else if (ch >= 0xE000 && ch <= 0xE864)                    \
24291       {                                   \
24292         cp = __ucs_to_gb18030_tab2[ch - 0xE000];                  \
24293         if ((cp[0] != 0 || cp[1] != 0) && cp[0] < 0x81)           \
24294           {                                   \
24295         idx = cp[0] * 256 + cp[1] + 7456;                 \
24296         len = 4;                              \
24297           }                                   \
24298         else if (cp[0] == 0 && cp[1] == 0)                    \
24299           len = 0;                                \
24300       }                                   \
24301     else if (ch >= 0xE865 && ch <= 0xF92B)                    \
24302       {                                   \
24303         idx = ch - 0x6557;                            \
24304         len = 4;                                  \
24305       }                                   \
24306     else if (ch >= 0xF92C && ch <= 0xFFE5)                    \
24307       {                                   \
24308         cp = __ucs_to_gb18030_tab2[ch - 0xE000 - 4295];           \
24309         if ((cp[0] != 0 || cp[1] != 0) && cp[0] < 0x81)           \
24310           {                                   \
24311         idx = cp[0] * 256 + cp[1] + 7456;                 \
24312         len = 4;                              \
24313           }                                   \
24314         else if (cp[0] == 0 && cp[1] == 0)                    \
24315           len = 0;                                \
24316       }                                   \
24317     else if (ch >= 0xFFE6 && ch <= 0xFFFF)                    \
24318       {                                   \
24319         idx = ch - 0x6604;                            \
24320         len = 4;                                  \
24321       }                                   \
24322     else if (ch == 0x20087)                           \
24323       cp = (const unsigned char *) "\xfe\x51";                \
24324     else if (ch == 0x20089)                           \
24325       cp = (const unsigned char *) "\xfe\x52";                \
24326     else if (ch == 0x200CC)                           \
24327       cp = (const unsigned char *) "\xfe\x53";                \
24328     else if (ch == 0x215d7)                           \
24329       cp = (const unsigned char *) "\xfe\x6c";                \
24330     else if (ch == 0x2298F)                           \
24331       cp = (const unsigned char *) "\xfe\x76";                \
24332     else if (ch == 0x241FE)                           \
24333       cp = (const unsigned char *) "\xfe\x91";                \
24334     else if (ch >= 0x10000 && ch <= 0x10FFFF)                 \
24335       {                                   \
24336         idx = ch + 0x1E248;                           \
24337         len = 4;                                  \
24338       }                                   \
24339     else                                      \
24340       len = 0;                                \
24341                                           \
24342     if (__builtin_expect (len, 2) == 0                    \
24343         || (len == 2 && __builtin_expect (cp[0], '\1') == '\0'))          \
24344       {                                   \
24345         /* Illegal character.  */                         \
24346         STANDARD_TO_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (4);                     \
24347       }                                   \
24348                                           \
24349     if (len == 2)                                 \
24350       {                                   \
24351         /* See whether there is enough room for the second byte we        \
24352            write.  */                             \
24353         if (cp[1] != '\0' && __builtin_expect (outptr + 1 >= outend, 0))  \
24354           {                                   \
24355         /* We have not enough room.  */                   \
24356         result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT;                     \
24357         break;                                \
24358           }                                   \
24359                                           \
24360         *outptr++ = cp[0];                            \
24361         if (cp[1] != '\0')                            \
24362           *outptr++ = cp[1];                          \
24363       }                                   \
24364     else /* len == 4 */                           \
24365       {                                   \
24366         /* See whether there is enough room for all four bytes we         \
24367            write.  */                             \
24368         if (__glibc_unlikely (outptr + 3 >= outend))              \
24369           {                                   \
24370         /* We have not enough room.  */                   \
24371         result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT;                     \
24372         break;                                \
24373           }                                   \
24374                                           \
24375         outptr[3] = (unsigned char)(idx % 10) + 0x30;             \
24376         idx /= 10;                                \
24377         outptr[2] = (unsigned char)(idx % 126) + 0x81;            \
24378         idx /= 126;                               \
24379         outptr[1] = (unsigned char)(idx % 10) + 0x30;             \
24380         outptr[0] = (unsigned char)(idx / 10) + 0x81;             \
24381         outptr += 4;                              \
24382       }                                   \
24383       }                                       \
24384                                           \
24385     inptr += 4;                                   \
24386   }
24387 #define LOOP_NEED_FLAGS
24388 #include <iconv/loop.c>
